    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level of 3 due to single compression-bending test condition; this gap is accepted given the focused scope of the COU and the availability of supplementary fatigue data in a separate COU. Normalized error metrics for all three QoIs fall within pre-specified acceptance bounds. Overall credibility is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA framework.",
